<TITLE> Banks drive stocks in New Year trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 1 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka stocks opened upbeat on the first day of the year 2008, mostly driven by bank shares. The market Tuesday opened with a vertical increase in the general index. It however fell in midday trade. At 12.06pm, the DGEN or general index rose 9.06 points or 0.3 percent to 3026.27. The DSI or all share price index edged up 7.33 points or 0.28 percent to 2543.29. The Dhaka Stock Exchange recorded turnover at Tk 746.96 million from transactions of 2,538,941 shares in the midday session. Market major Square Pharma appeared at the peak of the top share board by value at 12.03pm. Square was trading higher at Tk 3795 from the previous day's closing price at Tk 3682. AB Bank rose to Tk 2685 from Sunday's Tk 2561.25. Prime Bank climbed to Tk 932 from Tk 923.75. NBL was selling at Tk 1500 from Sunday's Tk 1494.25. Square Textile surged to Tk 129.6 from the previous day's closing price at Tk 127.4. Among other issues on the top share board by valueIFIC Bank, Islami Bank and Southeast Bankincreased on the DSE. BRAC Bank and UCBL fell on profit-taking. bdn
